params.valueOrId_: 授权的代币数量或NFT ID

returns._0: 永远会revert，返回类型只是为了符合接口要求

erc20Approve(address,uint256).details: 提供type(uint256).max作为授权值的结果是一个无限制的授权，      在转账时不会从该额度中扣除

erc20TransferFrom(address,address,uint25.details: 推荐使用此函数进行ERC20转账

erc721TransferFrom(address,address,uint2.details: 推荐使用此函数进行ERC721转账

getERC721QueueLength().details: 返回等待被转换为ERC721的代币ID数量

returns._0: 返回队列中存储的ERC721代币ID的数量

getERC721TokensInQueue(uint256,uint256).details: 从队列中获取从start_开始的count_个代币ID

returns._0: 返回指定范围内的代币ID数组

permit(address,address,uint256,uint256,u.details: 如果permit的value值设为type(uint256).max，将产生一个无限制的授权额度，      在转账时不会从该额度中扣除

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[ERC section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

transfer(address,uint256).details: This function assumes the operator is attempting to transfer as ERC-20      given this function is only supported on the ERC-20 interface.      Treats even large amounts that are valid ERC-721 ids as ERC-20s.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: 如果valueOrId是有效的代币ID，则该函数假定操作者试图转移ERC-721代币

DOMAIN_SEPARATOR().notice: Returns domain initial domain separator, or recomputes if chain id is not equal to initial chain id

depositTokens(uint256,address,uint256).notice: 向指定的 NFT 注入 ERC20 代币

depositTokens(uint256,uint256).notice: 向指定的NFT存入本合约的ERC20代币

erc721TransferExempt(address).notice: Function to check if address is transfer exempt

getERC721QueueLength().notice: 获取当前存储在队列中的ERC721代币数量

getERC721TokensInQueue(uint256,uint256).notice: 获取队列中指定范围的ERC721代币ID

getTokenDeposits(uint256).notice: 获取指定 NFT 的所有存款信息

ownerOf(uint256).notice: Function to find owner of a given ERC-721 token

withdrawTokens(uint256,uint256).notice: 从指定的 NFT 中提取 ERC20 代币
